<h3>idioms</h3>
<ul>
  <li>raw json data: GET <a href="/idioms/raw">/idioms/raw</a> (NB: this defaults to the according-to-sources idiom</li>
  <li>raw json data with spec: GET <a href="/idioms/raw?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance">/idioms/raw?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance</a> (NB: AXN=adverb singular plural, SC=standard candle)</li>
  <li>chart: GET <a href="/idioms/chart">/idioms/chart</a> (NB: this defaults to the according-to-sources idiom</li>
  <li>chart with spec (scaled by default: GET <a href="/idioms/chart?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance">/idioms/raw?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance</a> (NB: AXN=adverb singular plural, SC=standard candle)</li>
  <li>chart with spec unscaled: GET <a href="/idioms/chart?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance&unscaled=true">/idioms/raw?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance&unscaled=true</a> (NB: AXN=adverb singular plural, SC=standard candle)</li>
  <li>chart with spec unscaled, yaxis logarithmic: GET <a href="/idioms/chart?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance&unscaled=true&yaxistype=logarithmic">/idioms/raw?spec=AXN:according%20to,source,sources|SC:finance&unscaled=true&yaxistype=logarithmic</a> (NB: AXN=adverb singular plural, SC=standard candle)</li>
  <li>lots of individual phrases: GET <a href="/idioms/chart?unscaled=true&yaxistype=logarithmic&spec=SC:finance|SC:news|SC:business|SC:europe|SC:politics|SC:investors|SC:investor|SC:trump|SC:deutsche">/idioms/chart?unscaled=true&yaxistype=logarithmic&spec=SC:finance|SC:news|SC:business|SC:europe|SC:politics|SC:investors|SC:investor|SC:trump|SC:deutsche</a></li>
  <li>assorted idioms with plurals
    <ul>
      {{#each candidateChartSpecAndUrls as |specAndUrl|}}
        <li>chart with spec unscaled, yaxis logarithmic: <a href="{{{specAndUrl.url}}}">{{specAndUrl.spec}}</a></li>
      {{/each}}
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
Notes:
<ul>
  <li>AXN refers adverb/number/noun, and requires a csv of adverb text, singular noun, plural noun.</li>
  <li>SC refers to 'standard candle' (ref astronomy), and is just a standalone phrase. </li>
  <li>Multiple AXN and SC instances can be specified as pipe-separated, but probably best to only specify the one AXN, otherwise the graph will look messy.
  <li>If the query is 'scaled' (default, i.e. not unscaled=true), any specified SC values are averaged and used to scale non-ft.com site stats for the AXN.</li>
  <li>yaxistype=logarithmic is an alternative to scaling. </li>
</ul>
</p>

